byline.original: By ASHLEY SOUTHALL and SARAH WHEATON

abstract: A House veteran's retirement has made life easier for those in charge of eliminating a Congressional district, and a top challenger to Elizabeth Warren is bowing out.
snippet: A House veteran's retirement has made life easier for those in charge of eliminating a Congressional district, and a top challenger to Elizabeth Warren is bowing out.
lead_paragraph: Two Democrats announced decisions in Massachusetts today that drained a bit of suspense from the state's politics. Members of the state's House delegation who feared getting drawn out of their districts when one is stripped from the map breathed a sigh of relief as one of their own announced his retirement, and the Senate primary field narrowed.

headline.main: Two Massachusetts Democrats Say They Won't Run, Clarifying State Politics
